In England, in the seven days to 21 September, there were 171,146 new confirmed cases (302.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 September, there were 150,111 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 14% (21,035 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 26 September is 6,532,847 (11,552.3 cases per 100,000 population).
